CAPE TOWN - South African multinational telecommunications company, MTN has announced price changes to specific prepaid call rates which have taken effect today. The new call rate increase will however only affect certain price plan customers. This includes the MTB “Pay per second” and “Talk free” price plan customers.  ALSO READ: MTN cuts out-of-bundle data prices for rural South Africa TOP STORY: Transnet scored R10.4bn contract with South32 - BUSINESS REPORT ONLINE